chapters.title: Where Do People Get Their Guns

description:
A serious video this time, and a tough one to make. I hope some people find value in here somewhere, even if it's a less than perfect attempt. Even so, I think it was an important statement to make in the wake of the Parkland shooting.

Follow me on Twitter if you like: https://twitter.com/JoseNotAJay

My Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/JoseOnYoutube

A few sidenotes I should mention:
The 70% figure used in the paper describing where criminals in Chicago get their guns is made up of Family & Friends, but one third of that number includes "street" contacts. In other words people the buyer is familiar with, but may not count as a friend or family member. It's still considered a social connection though.

Sources cited are all linked below.
